            <p><strong>Question 5:</strong> A company evaluates customer satisfaction through survey data. If 60% of customers rated the service as "excellent" in January and this percentage dropped to 50% in February, what is the percentage decrease?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="solution">
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Percentage decrease = ((60 - 50) / 60) Ã— 100 = 16.67%.</p>
